No , in general there is a netting issue with French counterparties . The "quick fix" is to only permit ONE Transaction using a deemed ISDA . The broader issue to be resolved is that one of the parties must be a "financial institution" under French law . We tried to push ECT into that defintion , but without success . The next step is to require an opinion from outside counsel identifying our counterparty as that financial institution . ps - Tanya is well aware of the situation
