Yes , "eligible contract participant" ( "ECP" ) is an issue . Both ENA and ECTRI are Delaware corporations and are therefore subject to the jurisdiction of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission ( the U.S . regulatory agency with oversight for derivatives) . As a practical matter , I understand that ECTRI does have many executed ISDA agreements . I do not know the volume of "omnibus" trades . However , the ECTRI omnibus should have ECP representations in the annex .
