I don't know if Perry has responded to your request yet concerning what contracts are expiring with WTX Pool capacity and about that Duke contract you mentioned in our Staff Mtg yesterday , but I looked at my notes and this is what I come up with . The Duke contract that expires 7/31/2002 without ROFR is already taken into consideration as expired in the November , 2002 capacity of 17,300/d we derived last week ( which we've already sold 20,000/d to Calpine & PPL) . Other contracts expiring in 2002 & early 2003 from the WTX Pool are: Total 25,365/d Otherwise , we have WTX Pool capacity every Apr-Oct of 14,000/d ( opposite of SWG's seasonal ctrc) . The other issue we could take into consideration here is displacement . For the month of November , 2002 ( for example ) we have 22,000/d of capacity we are including in our WT-1 total that is made up of southward paths ( 20,000/d for USGT & 2,000/d for Astra with receipts north of WT-1 for delivery to WTX delivery points south of WT-2) . This is the most conservative capacity reservation policy . In the event not enought physical receipts were nominated south of WT-1 to fulfill all physical deliveries nominated south of WT-1 , we would need to compress gas south through WT-1 to make deliveries for these two contracts . We may want to reassess this .
